## Security policy + why your first SoapUI call failed

* SOAP trigger security policy was **Username Password Token**
* In SoapUI, you first tried **Basic Auth** → mismatch → got **401 Unauthorized**
* Fix:

  * Add SOAP Header:

    * **WS-Security UsernameToken**
* Token options:

  * **PasswordText** (password visible as text in header) ✅ worked in their instance
  * **PasswordDigest/hashed** (preferred in real-time; but trainer said digest wasn’t working in their demo environment)

Key takeaway:

> Don’t “try random auth methods.” Always check the **Trigger Connection → Security Policy** to know what format credentials must be in.

