## Interview-ready Q&A (based only on this session)

**Q1. Why can one REST trigger connection be reused for many APIs, but SOAP usually can’t?**
A: REST trigger connection doesn’t carry request/response structures; they’re defined per integration. SOAP trigger connection depends on WSDL and operations, so you typically need separate connections.

**Q2. Abstract vs Concrete WSDL?**
A: Abstract WSDL defines types/messages/operations/binding (spec), but no endpoint/service. Concrete WSDL adds service/endpoint URL after deployment.

**Q3. How do you know which auth to use when calling an OIC service?**
A: Check the **Integration’s Trigger Connection → Security Policy**. That dictates Basic Auth vs OAuth vs UsernameToken, etc.

**Q4. Can SOAP services be tested inside OIC like REST?**
A: No (as per session). Use the generated WSDL URL and test with external tools like SoapUI.

